18 PART II. MEDICAID COVERAGE OF FERTILITY CARE
19 SECTION 2.1.(a) The Department of Health and Human Services, Division of
20 Health Benefits, shall seek approval from the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services (CMS)
21 to implement Medicaid coverage for care. This coverage shall include fertility diagnostic care,
22 any medically necessary ovulation-enhancing drugs, and intrauterine insemination that is
23 intended to treat infertility and achieve a pregnancy that results in a live birth that includes at
24 least three cycles of ovulation-enhancing medication treatment over a Medicaid beneficiary's
25 lifetime.
26 SECTION 2.1.(b) There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department
27 of Health and Human Services, Division of Health Benefits, the sum of forty-five million dollars
28 ($45,000,000) in recurring funds and associated receipts beginning with the 2026-2027 fiscal
29 year to be used to implement the new coverage required under subsection (a) of this section.
30 SECTION 2.1.(c) This section becomes effective July 1, 2026.
31
32 PART III. EDUCATION TRAINING MODULE FOR CERTAIN LICENSING BOARDS
33 SECTION 3.1.(a) Article 1 of Chapter 90 of the General Statutes is amended by
34 adding a new section to read:
35 "§ 90-5.5. Certain continuing medical education requirements.
36 In addition to continuing medical education requirements required by the Board under this
37 Article, the Board shall make available to licensees an education training module in accordance
38 with this section. In developing the education training module, the Board shall consult experts in
39 lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, and queer family building, the American Society for
40 Reproductive Medicine, and the Society for Assisted Reproductive Technology. The education
41 training module shall provide training to encourage licensees to speak and have effective
42 discussions with their patients and families in an appropriate manner on all of the following:
43 (1) Prevention and elimination of discrimination based on sexual orientation and
44 expression in medical settings.
45 (2) Improving access to services for lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, and queer
46 individuals.
47 (3) Options for lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, and queer individuals seeking
48 to start or grow their family."
49 SECTION 3.1.(b) G.S. 90-171.42 reads as rewritten:
50 "§ 90-171.42. Continuing education programs.
